I think it's a good idea (RICE.EDU being a host name).  Currently we
have a host BRL.ARPA which doesn't exits, our internet gateways just
route packets for it to one of the hosts that participates in our global
mail name database.  That way, people can address stuff to user@BRL and
no one host must be up all the time to catch the incoming mail.  Under
the domain scheme it would seem very disappointing to have to use
BRL.BRL.MIL as our mail name when BRL.MIL would seem much more friendly.

-Ron

